                <head>348. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On February 5, Julian Amery, Under Secretary for Colonial Affairs, flew to
                    Nicosia to represent the British Government in a new series of discussions with
                    Archbishop <persName>Makarios</persName> over the issue of British bases on
                    Cyprus. <persName corresp="#p_AHJ1">Amery</persName> and
                        <persName>Makarios</persName> failed to reach an agreement and on February
                    8, the Governor of Cyprus announced that the date for the island’s independence
                    was further (and indefinitely) postponed. <persName corresp="#p_AHJ1"
                        >Amery</persName> returned to London on February 11 after further
                    unsuccessful discussions. On February 23, <persName corresp="#p_AHJ1"
                        >Amery</persName> returned to Nicosia to resume discussions with Archbishop
                        <persName>Makarios</persName> over the future of British bases on
                    Cyprus.</p>
            </div>
